button.description:
# component.button

## Description
Composant bouton fondamental du Design System supportant trois tailles (sm, md, lg) et états interactifs. Gère nativement les icônes, états désactivé/focus et transitions fluides via tokens de design.

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser les sizes prédéfinies (sm, md, lg) pour maintenir la cohérence typographique et spatiale

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas surcharger le bouton avec plus de 2 éléments enfants (texte + icône maximum)

## 💻 Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
import React from 'react';

const Button = ({
  size = 'md',
  children,
  disabled = false,
  icon = null,
  onClick,
  ...props
}) => {
  const sizeConfig = {
    sm: {
      paddingX: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      paddingY: 'var(--spacing-xs)',
      fontSize: 'var(--font-size-sm)',
      lineHeight: 'var(--font-line-height-normal)',
      gap: 'var(--spacing-xs)',
      minHeight: '32px',
      iconSize: '16px'
    },
    md: {
      paddingX: 'var(--spacing-md)',
      paddingY: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      fontSize: 'var(--font-size-sm)',
      lineHeight: 'var(--font-line-height-normal)',
      gap: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      minHeight: '40px',
      iconSize: '20px'
    },
    lg: {
      paddingX: 'var(--spacing-lg)',
      paddingY: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      fontSize: 'var(--font-size-md)',
      lineHeight: 'var(--font-line-height-normal)',
      gap: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      minHeight: '48px',
      iconSize: '24px'
    }
  };

  const config = sizeConfig[size];

  const buttonStyle = {
    display: 'inline-flex',
    alignItems: 'center',
    justifyContent: 'center',
    paddingLeft: config.paddingX,
    paddingRight: config.paddingX,
    paddingTop: config.paddingY,
    paddingBottom: config.paddingY,
    minHeight: config.minHeight,
    gap: config.gap,
    fontSize: config.fontSize,
    lineHeight: config.lineHeight,
    fontWeight: 'var(--font-weight-semibold)',
    fontFamily: 'var(--font-family-default)',
    borderRadius: 'var(--radius-md)',
    border: `var(--border-width-default) solid var(--semantic-color-action-primary-border-default)`,
    backgroundColor: disabled ? 'var(--semantic-color-action-primary-bg-disabled)' : 'var(--semantic-color-action-primary-bg-default)',
    color: disabled ? 'var(--semantic-color-action-primary-text-disabled)' : 'var(--semantic-color-action-primary-text-default)',
    cursor: disabled ? 'not-allowed' : 'pointer',
    transition: 'var(--transition)',
    opacity: disabled ? 0.6 : 1,
    outline: 'none'
  };

  const iconStyle = {
    width: config.iconSize,
    height: config.iconSize,
    display: 'flex',
    alignItems: 'center',
    justifyContent: 'center'
  };

  const handleFocus = (e) => {
    e.target.style.boxShadow = `0 0 0 var(--focus-ring-offset) var(--semantic-color-action-primary-bg-default), 0 0 0 calc(var(--focus-ring-offset) + var(--focus-ring-width)) var(--focus-ring-color)`;
  };

  const handleBlur = (e) => {
    e.target.style.boxShadow = 'none';
  };

  return (
    <button
      style={buttonStyle}
      disabled={disabled}
      onClick={onClick}
      onFocus={handleFocus}
      onBlur={handleBlur}
      {...props}
    >
      {icon && <span style={iconStyle}>{icon}</span>}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};

export default function ButtonShowcase() {
  return (
    <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '16px', alignItems: 'center', padding: '24px' }}>
      <Button size="sm">Small Button</Button>
      <Button size="md">Medium Button</Button>
      <Button size="lg">Large Button</Button>
      <Button size="md" disabled>Disabled</Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

input.description:
# component.input

## Description
Composant d'entrée de texte fondamental avec support multi-taille et états visuels distincts (défaut, hover, focus, erreur, disabled). Gère les variations de padding, hauteur minimale et apparence des bordures via tokens de design.

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser les 3 tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`) selon le contexte de mise en page

❌ **Don't**
- Combiner l'état `error` avec `disabled` simultanément

## 💻 Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const Input = ({ 
  size = 'md', 
  error = false, 
  disabled = false, 
  placeholder = 'Entrez du texte...',
  value = '',
  onChange = () => {},
  ...props 
}) => {
  const [isFocused, setIsFocused] = useState(false);

  const sizeConfig = {
    sm: {
      paddingX: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      paddingY: 'var(--spacing-xs)',
      fontSize: 'var(--font-size-sm)',
      minHeight: '32px',
    },
    md: {
      paddingX: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      paddingY: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      fontSize: 'var(--font-size-md)',
      minHeight: '40px',
    },
    lg: {
      paddingX: 'var(--spacing-md)',
      paddingY: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
      fontSize: 'var(--font-size-lg)',
      minHeight: '48px',
    },
  };

  const baseStyle = {
    ...sizeConfig[size],
    backgroundColor: disabled ? 'var(--color-bg-disabled)' : 'var(--color-bg-primary)',
    color: disabled ? 'var(--color-text-disabled)' : 'var(--color-text-primary)',
    borderWidth: 'var(--borderWidth-default)',
    borderStyle: 'solid',
    borderColor: error 
      ? 'var(--color-danger-500)' 
      : isFocused 
      ? 'var(--color-border-focus)' 
      : disabled 
      ? 'var(--color-border-disabled)' 
      : 'var(--color-border-default)',
    borderRadius: 'var(--radius-md)',
    outline: 'none',
    transition: 'border-color 200ms ease-in-out',
    cursor: disabled ? 'not-allowed' : 'text',
  };

  const placeholderStyle = {
    color: 'var(--color-text-tertiary)',
  };

  return (
    <input
      type="text"
      style={baseStyle}
      placeholder={placeholder}
      value={value}
      onChange={onChange}
      onFocus={() => setIsFocused(true)}
      onBlur={() => setIsFocused(false)}
      disabled={disabled}
      {...props}
    />
  );
};

export default function InputShowcase() {
  const [inputValue, setInputValue] = useState('');

  const containerStyle = {
    display: 'flex',
    flexDirection: 'column',
    gap: '24px',
    padding: '32px',
    fontFamily: 'system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif',
  };

  const rowStyle = {
    display: 'flex',
    gap: '16px',
    alignItems: 'flex-start',
  };

  const labelStyle = {
    fontSize: '12px',
    fontWeight: '600',
    color: 'var(--color-text-primary)',
    marginBottom: '8px',
  };

  const wrapperStyle = {
    flex: 1,
  };

  return (
    <div style={containerStyle}>
      <div style={rowStyle}>
        <div style={wrapperStyle}>
          <div style={labelStyle}>Size: SM</div>
          <Input size="sm" placeholder="Small input" />
        </div>
        <div style={wrapperStyle}>
          <div style={labelStyle}>Size: MD</div>
          <Input size="md" placeholder="Medium input" value={inputValue} onChange={(e) => setInputValue(e.target.value)} />
        </div>
        <div style={wrapperStyle}>
          <div style={labelStyle}>Size: LG</div>
          <Input size="lg" placeholder="Large input" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style={rowStyle}>
        <div style={wrapperStyle}>
          <div style={labelStyle}>Error State</div>
          <Input size="md" error={true} placeholder="Input with error" />
        </div>
        <div style={wrapperStyle}>
          <div style={labelStyle}>Disabled State</div>
          <Input size="md" disabled={true} placeholder="Disabled input" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

card.description:
# component.card

## Description
Composant conteneur fondamental offrant une surface encapsulée avec padding, bordure et ombre. Élément modulaire destiné à organiser du contenu hiérarchisé au sein de layouts complexes.

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser la Card comme wrapper principal pour grouper du contenu logiquement lié

❌ **Don't**
- Imbriquer plus de 2 niveaux de Cards sans justification métier

## 💻 Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
import React from 'react';

const Card = ({ 
  children, 
  variant = 'default',
  className = '',
  ...props 
}) => {
  // Styles liés aux tokens du Design System
  const baseStyle = {
    backgroundColor: 'var(--semantic-color-bg-primary)',
    borderRadius: 'var(--semantic-radius-lg)',
    border: `1px solid var(--semantic-color-border-default)`,
    boxShadow: 'var(--semantic-shadow-100)',
    boxSizing: 'border-box',
  };

  const paddingVariants = {
    default: { padding: 'var(--semantic-spacing-md)' },
    compact: { padding: 'var(--semantic-spacing-sm)' },
    spacious: { padding: 'var(--semantic-spacing-lg)' },
  };

  const cardStyle = {
    ...baseStyle,
    ...paddingVariants[variant],
  };

  return (
    <div 
      style={cardStyle}
      className={className}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

// ============ RENDER DE DÉMONSTRATION ============

export default function CardShowcase() {
  const containerStyle = {
    display: 'flex',
    gap: '24px',
    padding: '32px',
    flexWrap: 'wrap',
  };

  const textStyle = {
    fontSize: '14px',
    lineHeight: '1.5',
    color: 'var(--semantic-color-text-secondary)',
  };

  const titleStyle = {
    fontSize: '16px',
    fontWeight: '600',
    marginBottom: '8px',
    color: 'var(--semantic-color-text-primary)',
  };

  return (
    <div style={containerStyle}>
      <Card variant="compact">
        <div style={titleStyle}>Compact</div>
        <div style={textStyle}>Padding réduit pour contenu dense</div>
      </Card>

      <Card variant="default">
        <div style={titleStyle}>Default</div>
        <div style={textStyle}>Spacing standard recommandé</div>
      </Card>

      <Card variant="spacious">
        <div style={titleStyle}>Spacious</div>
        <div style={textStyle}>Padding étendu pour respiration</div>
      </Card>
    </div>
  );
}
```

badge.description:
# Badge

## Description
Composant de labellisation compacte destiné à mettre en évidence des statuts, des catégories ou des métadonnées. Utilise des tokens de spacing et typographie pour garantir une cohérence visuelle avec le Design System.

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser le Badge pour étiqueter des statuts courts (ex: "Nouveau", "En cours", "Approuvé")

❌ **Don't**
- Ne jamais y placer du contenu textuel long ou multi-lignes

## 💻 Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
import React from 'react';

const Badge = ({ children, variant = 'default' }) => {
  const badgeStyle = {
    display: 'inline-flex',
    alignItems: 'center',
    justifyContent: 'center',
    paddingLeft: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
    paddingRight: 'var(--spacing-sm)',
    paddingTop: 'var(--spacing-xs)',
    paddingBottom: 'var(--spacing-xs)',
    fontSize: 'var(--font-size-xs)',
    fontWeight: 'var(--font-weight-medium)',
    borderRadius: 'var(--radius-full)',
    whiteSpace: 'nowrap',
    backgroundColor: 'var(--semantic-color-neutral-bg-subtle)',
    color: 'var(--semantic-color-neutral-text-default)',
  };

  const variantStyles = {
    default: badgeStyle,
    success: {
      ...badgeStyle,
      backgroundColor: 'var(--semantic-color-success-bg-subtle)',
      color: 'var(--semantic-color-success-text-default)',
    },
    warning: {
      ...badgeStyle,
      backgroundColor: 'var(--semantic-color-warning-bg-subtle)',
      color: 'var(--semantic-color-warning-text-default)',
    },
    error: {
      ...badgeStyle,
      backgroundColor: 'var(--semantic-color-error-bg-subtle)',
      color: 'var(--semantic-color-error-text-default)',
    },
  };

  return (
    <span style={variantStyles[variant]}>
      {children}
    </span>
  );
};

export default function BadgeDemo() {
  return (
    <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '12px', alignItems: 'center' }}>
      <Badge variant="default">Nouveau</Badge>
      <Badge variant="success">Approuvé</Badge>
      <Badge variant="warning">En attente</Badge>
      <Badge variant="error">Rejeté</Badge>
    </div>
  );
}
```
